<p><pb

n="1v"/><!--
This is not explicitly stated anywhere I've read, but I assume that these double plates, each inscribed on one face only, use 1verso and 2 recto, with the blank side of each plate facing outward.
--><lb
n="1" break="no"/><g type="mangala"/>namo bhagavate nārāyaṇāya<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><space type="binding-hole"/> svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> śrīmati pravarddhamāna-vijaya<!--
The maṅgala symbol looks like a mirrored C. It is definitely inline.
--><lb
n="2" break="no"/>-rājya-sambatsara-śate nava-navaty-u<space type="binding-hole"/>ttare gupta-n<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>r̥</corr></choice>pa-rājya-bhuktau mahā<!--
Hira Lal emends to rājye but I think this is unnecessary.
--><lb
n="3" break="no"/>-mārggaśīrṣa-sambatsare kārttika-māsa-daśamyāṁ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> Asyāṁ sambatsara-māsa<lb
n="4" break="no"/>-divasa-pūrvvāyā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> caturddaśa-vidyā-sthāna-vidita-paramārthasya kapilasy<choice><sic>e</sic><corr>ai</corr></choice>va <lb
n="5"/>maharṣeḥ sarvva-ta<sic>tv</sic>a-jñasya bharadvāja-sagotrasya nr̥pati-pari<sic>b</sic>rājaka<lb
n="6" break="no"/>-suśarmmaṇaḥ kulotpannena mahārāja-śrī-devāḍhya-puttra-pranaptrā mahā<lb
n="7" break="no"/>rāja-śrī-prabhañjana-pranaptrā mahārāja-śrī-dāmodara-naptrā go-sahasra<lb
n="8" break="no"/>-hasty-aśva-hiraṇyāneka-bhūm<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>-pradasya guru-pitr̥-mātr̥-pūj<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>-tatparasyāneka<lb
n="9" break="no"/>-samara-śata-vijayinaḥ sāṣṭādaśāṭavī-rājyābhyantaraṁ <unclear>ḍa</unclear>bhālā-rājyaṁ sama<!--
Fleet reads the toponym as ḍabhālā or ḍahālā in IN00081/8 and equates it to a toponym known to him as Ḍāhala, Ḍāhāla, Ḍahāla or Ḍahalā, "which seems to represent the modern Bundêlkhaṇḍ, and which was in later times a province of the Haihayas or Kalachuris of Tripura near Jabalpur" (Fleet_1888:114).
--><lb
n="10" break="no"/>nupālayi<unclear>ṣ</unclear>ṇ<unclear>o</unclear>r aneka-guṇa-vikhyāta-yaśasaḥ śrī-mahārāja-hastinaḥ sutena
<lb
n="11"/>varṇṇāśrama-dharmma-sthāpanābhiratena parama-bhāgavatenātyanta-pitr̥-bhaktena <lb
n="12"/>sva-va<sic>ṅ</sic>ś<unclear>ā</unclear>moda-kareṇa mahārāja-śrī-saṁkṣobhe<sic>n</sic>a mātā-pittror ātmanaś ca puṇyā<lb
n="13" break="no"/>bhivr̥ddhy-arthaṁ tripurī-viṣaye prastaravāṭaka-grāmasya ArddhaM dvāravati<lb
n="14" break="no"/>kāyāś ca caturtho <sic>ṅ</sic>śaḥ Evam etau pūrvvāghāṭa-pariccheda-maryyā<!--
The halanta character is almost full size, with a line above.
--><pb

n="2r"/><lb
n="15" break="no"/>dayā bhāradvāja-sagotrāya mādhyandina-vāj<sic>i</sic>saneya-sabra<unclear>hma</unclear><lb
n="16" break="no"/>cāriṇe brāhmaṇa-bhānusvāmine puttra-pauttrānvayopabhogyau Etau <lb
n="17"/>sodraṅgau soparikarau A-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāv<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>e</corr></choice>śyau cora-drohaka-varjjaM tāmra<!--
The halanta character is almost full size, with a line above.
--><lb
n="18" break="no"/>-śāsanena Āgrahārau Atisr̥ṣṭau </p>
<p>tad asmat-kulotthair mmat-pāda-piṇḍopa<lb
n="19" break="no"/>jīvibhir vvā kālāntareṣv api na vyāghātaḥ karaṇīyaḥ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> Evam <choice><sic>ājñāpta</sic><corr>ājñapte</corr></choice> yo <lb
n="20"/>nyathā kuryāt tam ahaṁ dehāntara-gato pi mahatāvadhyānena nirddaheyaṁ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> Uktaṁ ca <lb
n="21"/>bhagavatā paramarṣiṇā veda-vyāsena vyāsena </p>
<lg n="1" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">pūrvva-dattāṁ dvijātibhyo</l>
<l n="b">yatnāT<lb
n="22"/>rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira<!--
The halanta T character is reduced in size, with a line above.
--></l>
<l n="c">mah<sic>im</sic> mahimatāṁ śreṣṭha</l>
<l n="d">dānāc chreyo nupālanaṁ</l>
</lg>
<lg n="2" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">bahubhiḥ <lb
n="23"/>vasudhā bhuktā</l>
<l n="b">rājabhiḥ sagarādibhiḥ</l>
<l n="c">yasya yasya yadā bhūmiḥ</l>
<l n="d">tasya <lb
n="24"/>tasya tadā phalaṁ</l>
</lg>
<lg n="3" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">ṣaṣṭiṁ varṣa-sahasrāṇi</l>
<l n="b">svargg<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>e</corr></choice> modati bhūmidaḥ</l>
<l n="c">Acchettā <lb
n="25"/>cānumantā ca</l>
<l n="d">tāny eva narake vaseT</l>
</lg>
<lg n="4" met="upajāti">
<l n="a">bhūmi-pradānān na paraṁ pradānaM</l>
<l n="b"><lb
n="26"/>dānād viśiṣṭaṁ paripālana<sic>n</sic> tu</l>
<l n="c">sarvve tisr̥ṣṭāṁ paripālya bhūmiṁ</l>
<l n="d">nr̥pā <lb
n="27"/>nr̥gādyāḥ tridivaṁ prapannā Iti</l>
</lg>
<p>likh<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>tañ ca jīvita-naptrā bhujaṅga<lb
n="28" break="no"/>dāsa-puttreṇa vyāpāraṇay<unclear>a</unclear> īśvaradāsena<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> dūtakaḥ puna<lb
n="29" break="no"/>rvvasuḥ</p>
<p>sambatsara <num value="199"><g type="numeral">100</g> <unclear><g type="numeral">90</g> 9</unclear></num> mahāmārgga-varṣe kārttika di <num value="10"><g type="numeral">10</g></num><!--
The numeral is not really legible because of a hole in the plate, but the reading 90 9 is quite probable as the same is said in words in l2.
--></p>
